cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI 

The paper discusses empirical game-theoretical analysis and computational learning models for finding Nash equilibria in games based on partial knowledge of the game. This topic falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also discusses the query complexity of learning equilibria, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.SI).
